<item>
            <title>[LU-20138] FLR-EC: Reword &quot;stripe set&quot; to &apos;data stripe unit&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20138</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Once the full EC series has landed, reword and harmonize terms like &lt;br/&gt;
stripe set -&amp;gt; data stripe unit&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
How does this terminology compare to existing RAID publications/implementations? As much as possible, we should use the same terminology to describe the EC implementation to minimize confusion. In &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.pdl.cmu.edu/PDL-FTP/Declustering/ASPLOS.pdf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.pdl.cmu.edu/PDL-FTP/Declustering/ASPLOS.pdf&lt;/a&gt; it refers to this as a &quot;data stripe unit&quot;, and has a &quot;parity stripe unit&quot; for the parity.&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will touch a lot of different parts that are from different patches, many of which have not yet landed, so defer until they have all landed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
